node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Recovery and Resilience
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. Being able to recognize one of these wounds, and using positive language when discussing it, supports a positive culture across the Department of the Air Force and could save a life. It is important for Airmen and Guardians to seek help for invisible wounds, taking that first step towards recovery.
.
This video describes the importance of Airmen and Guardians seeking help for invisible wounds and how taking that first step towards recovery results in positive outcomes and enhanced resilience.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources
.
Over the past five years, United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has implemented solutions that drive timely, proactive case handling, equitable, informed interactions and decisions, engaged leadership and a supportive environment, and accessible, effective care delivery. 
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. The impact of invisible wounds and can develop at any time, in any place, in or out of uniform.
.
Learn more at: https://go.usa.gov/xszpN
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Signs and Symptoms
.
Since its inception in 2016, the United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has been a leader in creating a supportive culture for #Airmen living with invisible wounds. Being able to recognize an invisible wound could save a life. Airman can learn to see the signs and symptoms of invisible wounds in others that they may see in themselves.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Air Force Chief of Staff Gen. Charles Q. Brown, Jr., & @cmsaf_official discuss how empowering Airmen will lead to success in building the future Air Force today. They also discussed Accelerate Change or Lose, the Action Orders, leadership and followership, how to rise above bias & self-limitations, and the future of the #AirForce.
.
The primary focus of this call was to connect with Airmen across the world, and give insight to how the Action orders, new Air Force missions statement and developmental guidance are being implemented for the Total Force.
.
#RealTalk #CoffeeTalk #Future #Empowerment #Questions

node.text: Flying, fighting and winning since 1947. #USAF73

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 23, 2021. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text:
Looking for the needle in the hay stack.
.
Airmen 1st Class Lainey Harmon, left, and Elaine Arceneaux, 60th Logistics Readiness Squadron materiel management aircraft parts store technicians, check parts in storage racks at @travisafb, California. The 60th LRS Materiel Management Flight is responsible for managing inventory. They administer and operate complex supply systems to ensure financial accountability for all of the utilized supplies. These Airmen ensure every asset — from small screws to multimillion-dollar machinery — is accounted for and where it needs to be whenever our Airmen need them. 
.
📷  by Nicholas Pilch
.
#logistics #aircraft #maintenance

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 23, 2021. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Saving lives at home and abroad⚕️ 
.
Staff Sgt. Dwayne Baldwin, 701st Airlift Squadron loadmaster, inspects cargo before departing to Johan Adolf Pengel International Airport, Suriname, from Joint Base Charleston, South Carolina. The portable field hospital was donated by @ussouthcom to the Suriname Ministry of Health to boost their overwhelmed medical capacity brought on by COVID-19. 
.
📸 by Staff Sgt. Shawn White
.
@teamcharleston

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 22, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Sleep tight; we got you covered 🌑
.
A pararescueman from the 82nd Expeditionary Rescue Squadron checks for explosives during a mass casualty exercise in the Combined Joint Task Force – Horn of Africa AOR. Mass casualty exercises prepare pararescuemen and support personnel for potential real world operations with large numbers of casualties. 
.
📸 by Senior Airman Cydnie Williams

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 22, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, aircraft and outdoors.

node.text:
Your ride has arrived 🛫 
.
A Ukranian Armed Forces dog handler observes a U.S. Air Force CV-22 Osprey during #ExerciseSeaBreeze 21 at an undisclosed location. 
.
Exercise Sea Breeze is an annual event that brings together military units from several countries, and within 2d Marine Expeditionary Force, to enhance their warfighting capabilities and build strong relationships. 
.
@eucomofficial #CV22 #ospreyaircraft

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
Locked in 🛩 
.
A KC-135 Stratotanker in-flight refueling specialist assigned to the 340th Expeditionary Aircraft Refueling Squadron concentrates on refueling an F-16 Fighting Falcon over Southwest Asia. The KC-135 Stratotanker delivers U.S. Air Forces Central a global aerial refueling capability to support joint and coalition aircraft throughout the U.S. Central Command area of responsibility. 
.
📸 by Staff Sgt. Trevor T. McBride

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, outdoors and text that says 'FIRE'.

node.text:
Ready to serve🚶 
.
Senior Airman Bryce Gryder, 380th Expeditionary Fire Department firefighter, walks on the flightline during an exercise at Al Dhafra Air Base, United Arab Emirates. The fire department trained on the ability to use rescue tools to execute an emergency extrication during the exercise.
.
📸 by Staff Sgt. Jao’Torey Johnson
.
#firefighter #militaryphotography

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
Wait, so you DON'T pay bills in your chem gear?
.
Staff Sgt. Jordan Stinson, 628th Comptroller Squadron financial analyst, looks over simulated financial purchases after a chemical attack exercise during Palmetto Challenge at McEntire Joint National Guard Base, S.C. 

The exercise aimed to develop and maintain full-spectrum readiness and ensure JB Charleston’s Airmen were ready for rapid mobilization while supporting Air Mobility Command and @deptofdefense priorities. Both active-duty and reserve Airmen from the 628th Air Base Wing, 437th Airlift Wing and 315th Airlift Wing came together to train in an austere environment. More than 140 Airmen took part in the global mobilization readiness training at McEntire Joint National Guard Base, S.C. 
.
📸 by Senior Airman Cody R. Miller
.
@airnationalguard 
.
#portrait #militaryphotography #USAF

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 20, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Early bird gets the worm. 
.
A 63rd Aircraft Maintenance Unit maintainer performs a post-flight inspection on an F-35A Lightning II after a mission at Luke Air Force Base, Arizona. Crew chiefs perform nose-to-tail inspections after each flight to ensure aircraft are ready for the next day’s training. Luke AFB is the largest F-35 training base in the U.S. Air Force, providing combat ready Airmen and pilots.
.
📸 by Senior Airman Alexander Cook
.
#silhouette #sunrise #aviationphotography

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 19, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, military uniform and outdoors.

node.text:
Not a hair out of place.
.
Basic Cadet trainees from the class of 2025 march out to U.S. Air Force Academy's Jacks Valley in Colorado Springs, Colo., for field training.
.
📸 by Joshua Armstrong
.
#militaryphotography #USAFA #symmetry

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 19, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and outdoors.

node.text:
Up + ɹǝʌo 
.
Airmen assigned to the @ohionationalguard's 178th Wing Security Forces Squadron conduct wartime skills training at the Volk Field Combat Regional Training Center, Wisc. The Airmen  improved many of their tactics and marksmanship skills using long range distance targets, land navigation, night operations, dismounted patrolling, tactical combat casualty care and leadership development.
.
#teamwork #nationalguard

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 18, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
Sunday stroll 
.
F-15C Eagles assigned to the 493rd Fighter Squadron taxi prior to a training sortie in support of @NATO Air Policing operations at Keflavik Air Base, Iceland. NATO Air Policing is a peacetime collective defensive mission that safeguards the integrity of NATO alliance members’ airspace. 
.
📸 by Staff Sgt. Rachel Maxwell
.
#aircraftphotography #F15C

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on July 18, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, military uniform and outdoors.

node.text:
When the whole squad is fresh >>>
.
Airmen from the 422nd Security Forces Squadron gear up prior to a tri-agency active shooter response exercise at RAF Croughton, England. These Airmen worked with police officers from the Northamptonshire Police Department and the @ministryofdefence. They also participated in multiple exercises to enhance their search and seizure tactics, strengthen local ties and gain rapport with their fellow officers. 
.
📸 by Senior Airman Eugene Oliver
.
@501csw #training #partnership
